@title FHE Anti-Patterns
 @notice Demonstrates common mistakes and how to avoid them
 @dev Educational contract showing what NOT to do with FHE
 This contract intentionally contains anti-patterns for educational purposes.
 DO NOT use these patterns in production!
 Common Mistakes Covered:
 1. View functions with encrypted values (not allowed)
 2. Missing FHE.allowThis() permissions
 3. Incorrect handle lifecycle management
 4. Improper access control
 5. Gas inefficiencies

@notice CORRECT PATTERN: State-changing function for FHE operations
 @dev ✅ CORRECT: Use regular function, not view

@notice CORRECT PATTERN: Keep values encrypted on-chain
 @dev ✅ CORRECT: Only decrypt off-chain or when explicitly needed

@notice CORRECT PATTERN: Validate input proofs
 @dev ✅ CORRECT: Always validate encrypted inputs

@notice CORRECT PATTERN: Use FHE.select for conditional logic
 @dev ✅ CORRECT: Work with encrypted booleans properly

@notice CORRECT PATTERN: Efficient batch processing

expression.value:
FHE Best Practices:
1. Never use view functions for FHE operations
2. Always call FHE.allowThis() before using encrypted values
3. Grant users permission with FHE.allow() after operations
4. Implement access control even for encrypted data
5. Minimize number of FHE operations for gas efficiency
6. Track handle updates after each operation
7. Keep values encrypted on-chain
8. Always validate input proofs
9. Use FHE.select() for conditional logic
10. Optimize batch operations

contract showing what NOT to do with FHE This contract intentionally contains anti-patterns for educational purposes. DO NOT use these patterns in production! Common Mistakes Covered: 1. View functions with encrypted values (not allowed) 2. Missing FHE.allowThis() permissions 3. Incorrect handle lifecycle management 4. Improper access control 5. Gas inefficiencies","kind":"dev","methods":{"antiPattern10_InefficientBatch(bytes32[])":{"details":"\u274c WRONG: Processing array items one by one Why it's wrong: - FHE operations are expensive - Should batch when possible - Optimize for gas efficiency"},"antiPattern1_ViewFunctionWithEncryption(bytes32,bytes32)":{"details":"\u274c WRONG: Cannot perform FHE operations in view functions Why it's wrong: - View functions cannot modify state or perform FHE operations - FHE operations require transaction context - This will always fail in real FHEVM"},"antiPattern2_MissingAllowThis(bytes32)":{"details":"\u274c WRONG: Contract needs permission to use encrypted values Why it's wrong: - Contract must be granted permission via FHE.allowThis() - Without permission, cannot perform operations on encrypted data - Will fail with \"permission denied\" error"},"antiPattern3_NoUserPermission(address)":{"details":"\u274c WRONG: Users need permission to decrypt their data Why it's wrong: - After FHE operations, new handles are created - Users cannot decrypt new handles without explicit permission - Must call FHE.allow(result, user) to grant access"},"antiPattern4_NoAccessControl(address)":{"details":"\u274c WRONG: Anyone can read encrypted values Why it's wrong: - Even encrypted values should have access control - Prevents unauthorized decryption attempts - Protects user privacy"},"antiPattern5_InefficientOperations(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32)":{"details":"\u274c WRONG: Unnecessary intermediate variables and operations Why it's wrong: - Each FHE operation is expensive - Should minimize number of operations - Combine operations when possible"},"antiPattern6_IncorrectHandleLifecycle(bytes32)":{"details":"\u274c WRONG: Not understanding handle creation and expiration Why it's wrong: - Each FHE operation creates new handle - Old handles become invalid after operations - Must track and update handle references"},"antiPattern8_NoInputProofValidation(bytes32)":{"details":"\u274c WRONG: Not validating encrypted inputs Why it's wrong: - Input proofs ensure data integrity - Without validation, malicious inputs possible - Security vulnerability"},"antiPattern9_DirectBooleanComparison(bytes32,bytes32)":{"details":"\u274c WRONG: FHE comparisons return encrypted booleans Why it's wrong: - FHE.eq() returns ebool, not bool - Cannot use in if statements directly - Must use FHE.select() for conditional logic"},"bestPracticesSummary()":{"details":"Reference function listing all correct patterns"},"correctPattern10_EfficientBatch(bytes32[])":{"details":"\u2705 CORRECT: Optimize batch operations"},"correctPattern1_StatefulFHEOperation(bytes32,bytes32)":{"details":"\u2705 CORRECT: Use regular function, not view"},"correctPattern2_WithAllowThis(bytes32)":{"details":"\u2705 CORRECT: Always call FHE.allowThis() before operations"},"correctPattern3_WithUserPermission(address)":{"details":"\u2705 CORRECT: Always use FHE.allow() for user access"},"correctPattern4_WithAccessControl(address)":{"details":"\u2705 CORRECT: Verify caller permissions"},"correctPattern5_EfficientOperations(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32)":{"details":"\u2705 CORRECT: Minimize FHE operations"},"correctPattern6_CorrectHandleLifecycle(bytes32)":{"details":"\u2705 CORRECT: Always use the latest handle"},"correctPattern7_KeepEncrypted(bytes32)":{"details":"\u2705 CORRECT: Only decrypt off-chain or when explicitly needed"},"correctPattern8_WithInputProofValidation(uint32,bytes)":{"details":"\u2705 CORRECT: Always validate encrypted inputs"},"correctPattern9_UseSelect(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32,bytes32)":{"details":"\u2705 CORRECT: Work with encrypted booleans properly"}},"stateVariables":{"decryptedValue":{"details":"\u274c WRONG: Storing decrypted values defeats FHE purpose Why it's wrong: - Decrypted values are public on blockchain - Defeats entire purpose of FHE - Privacy is lost permanently"}},"title":"FHE
